HEADWORD: catalase
<hw>catalase</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>an enzyme found in most plant and
animal cells that functions as an oxidative catalyst; it decomposes
hydrogen peroxide into hydrogen and water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

